1. tree-sitter-aozora generated parser
================================================================================

`crates/tree-sitter-aozora/src/parser.c` (and accompanying header) is a
machine-generated artifact produced by tree-sitter
(https://tree-sitter.github.io/) from the hand-written `grammar.js` in
the same crate. The generated C is checked in so downstream consumers
(VS Code extension, LSP server, third-party editors) do not need a
tree-sitter CLI on their build machine. The grammar source is
Apache-2.0 OR MIT (the aozora-tools default); the tree-sitter generator
itself is MIT, see https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter for the
generator license.


================================================================================
2. Aozora Bunko sample works (public domain)
================================================================================

`samples/tsumi-to-batsu-x100.afm` is a dev-only ~200 MB stress fixture
(Fyodor M. Dostoyevsky's 『罪と罰』 in the Japanese translation by
米川正夫 (Masao Yonekawa), repeated 100×), gitignored and built locally
from the public Aozora Bunko text. Aozora Bunko card number 56656
(https://www.aozora.gr.jp/cards/001485/card56656.html). Public domain:
the author died in 1881 and the translator in 1966; the Japanese
translation copyright has lapsed under Japanese law. The fixture is
not redistributed in this repository — it is reconstituted on the
developer's machine on demand for benchmarks.

All other files under `samples/` are original hand-written aozora
notation by the aozora-tools contributors and are dual-licensed under
the same terms as the rest of this repository.


